Vec3

public Vec3(Vec4 v)

Wraps a Quaternion (4D Vector) into a 3D one.
This happens by scaling the fourth component of the Vec4 by the three other components
This forces a simplification of the quaternion

Parameters:
v - Quaternion to wrap

multiply

public final Vec3 multiply(Vec3 v)
Deprecated. 


Multiply isn't an accurate enough description of what this function should do, cross() or dot() should be used instead.
Included for identification of multiplication terms. Most multiplication is cross product anyway, which is what this method does.

Parameters:
v - Vector to multiply
Returns:
Vector resulting of the cross product

divide

public final Vec3 divide(float d)

Another method to try to avoid.
It will happily do what you want but usually there is a better way of doing it.
Un-scales a value by a given amount by multiplying all components by the inversion of the given value

Parameters:
d - Value to divide by
Returns:
scaled Vector
